text: The briefing was the most thorough update on Trump’s health since he revealed his positive test. But the comments immediately triggered a flurry of questions about whether Trump and the W.H. had misled the public about the circumstances of the diagnosis https://t.co/sSqyjyFQgh

name: politico
text: Members of Trump’s medical team said it had been 48 hours since Trump started a key element of his treatment and 72 hours since he was diagnosed with coronavirus. But Trump revealed his status early Friday morning — about 36 hours before today's briefing https://t.co/aWQXY5TYLY

name: politico
text: At his briefing Conley revealed for the first time specifics on some of Trump’s vitals, noting that his blood pressure and heart rate were both within Trump’s normal range. He also discussed the president's risk factors. https://t.co/sSqyjyFQgh https://t.co/XwDDMhA2I6

name: politico
text: To this point, Trump’s only public appearance related to his condition has been a brief, 18-second video he released before going to Walter Reed, thanking his supporters and proclaiming, “I think I’m doing very well” https://t.co/sSqyjyFQgh

name: politico
text: Trump has completed an infusion of an experimental antibody drug produced by Regeneron — receiving the highest dosage being tested in the ongoing clinical trial — and is taking aspirin, zinc and vitamin D https://t.co/JBKPC6C9tj

name: politico
text: Conley also said Trump’s oxygen saturation — the level of the gas in his blood — was 96 percent, squarely within the normal range https://t.co/sSqyjyoeRH https://t.co/3XKWX8Xg3b
